text: The 2018–19 Moldovan Women Top League season in association football was the 19th since its establishment. The season began on 2 September 2018 and ended on 26 May 2019. Agarista-ȘS Anenii Noi were the defending champions. ==Teams== {| class="wikitable sortable" |- !Club !Location |- | Agarista-ȘS || Anenii Noi |- | Alga || Tiraspol |- | Belceanka || Bălți |- | ȘS Ciobruciu-GTC || Cioburciu |- | LTPS-2 || Chișinău |- | Maksimum || Cahul |- | Narta-ȘS || Drăsliceni |- | Noroc || Nimoreni |- | ȘS 11-Real Succes || Chișinău |} ==Format== The schedule consists of two rounds, each team plays each other once home-and-away for a total of 16 matches per team. ==League table== === Results === ==References== ==External links== *Women Top League - Moldova - Results, fixtures, tables - FMF Moldovan Women Top League 2018-19 Category:Moldovan Women Top League seasons Moldova
